description:
Responsibilities:


Copy-write and edit marketing brochures, executive speeches, statements to media and press releases;
Print & produce of all event-related materials such as brochures, flyers, preview, posters, catalogue and post-show reports, e-newsflash, e-flyer, e-card;
Develop and execute advertising planning, media buying and advertisement production;
Responsible for media relations and organization of press conferences;
Provide onsite media support such as exhibitor and visitor interview, media tour, photography and videography, executive interview;
Arrange incentive trips for foreign journalists to Hong Kong and China.

Requirements:

Degree holder in any disciplines, preferably in Public Relations or Communications;
At least 3 years' relevant experience in Public Relations or Marketing Communications, preferably with strong contacts to media in Hong Kong;
English native speaker is an advantage;
Able to interact positively and effectively with employees at all levels within the organization, as well as customers, prospects, and vendors;
A good team player with strong organizational skill and capable of working under pressure;
Detail-minded and results oriented;
Excellent media relations and copy-writing skills are preferable;
Good command of both written and spoken English and Mandarin and Cantonese;
Knowledgeable in Microsoft Office, Chinese Word Processing;
Willing to travel overseas;
Candidates with lesser experience will be considered as a position of Assistant Public Relations Officer.

 We work 5 days per week
We offer long-term career development opportunities, attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits including 5-day work, group life and medical insurance to right candidates. Interested parties please send full resume stating our reference number, present and expected salary to HR @hongkong.messefrankfurt.com or fax to 2511-5112.  

Messe Frankfurt (HK) Ltd. is an equal opportunity employer and is awarded the Good MPF Employer Award. Information provided will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for recruitment purpose. Candidates not invited for interview within 4 weeks may consider their application unsuccessful. However, we will retain the applications for a maximum period of 6 months and may refer them to suitable openings.

Job Duties:

Support the department in English and Chinese editorial needs;
Monitor media coverage to provide analysis and insights;
Conduct research on public affairs to provide market intelligence;
Participate in organizing corporate and media events;
Assist in building and maintaining good relationships with key stakeholders;
Provide administrative support to the department;
Support any ad-hoc duties as and when required.

Requirements:

Degree holder in Translations, English Studies, Mass Communications or related disciplines;
Preferably has 1 year of relevant working experience but fresh graduate with a strong desire to learn will also be considered;
Excellent command of written and spoken English and Chinese, conversant in Mandarin is preferred;
Strong PC skills, familiar with creative software is preferable;
Team player, good interpersonal and communications skills.

We offer long-term career prospect and competitive remuneration package to the appointed candidate. Please apply in confidence with your detailed resume stating your current and expected salary to Group Human Resources Department

by email to recruit(at)shuntakgroup.com

or mail to Penthouse 39/F, West Tower, Shun Tak Centre, 200 Connaught Road Central, Hong Kong

(Please quote reference number and applied position)

The information supplied by the applicants will be used in accordance with the Personal Data (Privacy) Policy of Shun Tak Group (a copy of which will be provided upon request). Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.


www.shuntakgroup.com

The Roles

Coordinate, execute and support a variety of corporate and marketing communications activities, public relations and promotion initiatives;
Drive and deliver a range of marketing communication materials, including but not limited to speeches, press release and media kit, corporate collaterals and enewsletter, editorial and publishing projects, marketing and social media content, surveys and research, etc.;
Monitor and uphold branding and corporate identity of HKDC and its affiliated programmes;
Manage corporate assets including printed collaterals, digital, visual and video content and online platforms e.g. website, social media channels and email database;
Work with internal and external parties for the production of HKDC Annual Report, publications and marketing collaterals;
Effectively handle the logistics and coordination of corporate visits and and provide onsite support to corporate events / activities;
Work with internal stakeholders and external parties and vendors on a variety of HKDC initiatives;
Manage the overall communication plan and logistics of the corporate membership and partnership programmes; and
Carry out other ad hoc projects and duties as assigned.

  Requirements

University graduate in Marketing, Communications, Journalism or Translation;
Minimum 5 years of relevant work experience in marketing, corporate communications or public relations;
Excellent copywriting and translation skills in both English and Chinese, with fluent spoken English, Cantonese and Putonghua;
Digital savvy, creative and passionate about communications, with sound knowledge of different social media and communications platforms and trends;
A self-motivated team-player with strong attention to detail; and
Mature, outgoing multi-tasker with good organisational and project management skills.


Interested parties are invited to apply by sending your resume with full details of education, work experience, current & expected salary, contact telephone number and earliest available date to the Human Resources Office, Hong Kong Design Centre, Unit 602, 6/F, Mill 5, The Mills, 45 Pak Tin Par Street, Tsuen Wan or by clicking “Apply Now” or email to: hr[@]hkdesigncentre.org on or before 28 January 2022. HKDC reserves the right not to make appointment for the post(s) advertised. Only short-listed candidates will be notified. All information received will be kept in strict confidence for six months and data will only be used for recruitment purpose.

Key Responsibilities

Provide editorial and event management support in all publicity related assignments;
Support the department in English and Chinese editorial needs, including corporate materials and marketing write-ups;
Act as key liaison between external stakeholders and internal departments to ensure communication objective are met;
Supervise the team in day-to-day assignments and manage departmental calendar effectively;
Support building digital capability across the enterprise and act as custodian of all online assets;
Research and collect information on industry and public affairs to keep the company abreast of market developments;
Assist in ad-hoc projects as assigned.

Requirement

Bachelor Degree holder, preferably in Translations, English Studies, Mass Communications or related disciplines;
Minimum 10 years of solid experience in media, corporate communications, public affairs, or research and analysis, preferably in sizable company or news outlet;
At least 2 years’ experience in supervisory role in reputable organization is preferred;
Excellent command of written and spoken English and Chinese, conversant in Mandarin is preferred;
Strong PC skills, familiar with creative software is preferable;
Must have solid media experience and proven track record in handling large scale events;
Good interpersonal and communications skills; team player and meticulous;
Candidate with lesser experience will be considered for an Assistant Manager position.

We offer long-term career prospect and competitive remuneration package to the appointed candidate. Please apply in confidence with your detailed resume stating your current and expected salary to Group Human Resources Department

by email to recruit(at)shuntakgroup.com

or mail to Penthouse 39/F, West Tower, Shun Tak Centre, 200 Connaught Road Central, Hong Kong

(Please quote reference number and applied position)

The information supplied by the applicants will be used in accordance with the Personal Data (Privacy) Policy of Shun Tak Group (a copy of which will be provided upon request). Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.


www.shuntakgroup.com

My client is a young and fast-growing startup well-funded by strategic investors and the HKSAR government. They are looking for a Social Media Editor/Digital Content Editor

Responsibilities


Manage and create content for various social media platforms (Facebook, Instagram, YouTube), including copywriting, image and basic video editing;
Closely monitor social media channels for timely response to comments and inquiries from audiences;
Manage budget spent on social media promotion and pay-per-click (PPC) advertising;
Monitor, analyze, and provide insight on social media platform activities;
Contribute visual and copywriting ideas for editorial, marketing and advertising projects;
Assist in maintaining and updating website content and other marketing duties as assigned.

Requirements


Fun and creative;
Degree holder in any related disciplines (i.e. Creative Design / Marketing / e-Commerce / Communications);
2-5 year experience in social media marketing or content creative field;
Knowledge or experience in properties, home renovation or interior design is a plus;
Familiar with digital media solutions (Social media, Facebook advertising, Google Analytics, SEO and SEM) is a plus;
Proficiency in AI and Photoshop;
Strong interest in social trends.

Job Responsibilities

Develop creative content strategy to meet client's marketing needs;
Create contents on digital platforms, including Facebook, Instagram, Weibo etc.;
To ensure all copy and information is accurate and meets commercial standard;
Research online behaviours and trends of the target audience
Monitor and report SEO performance and metrics, using web analytics tools and dashboards
Keeping updated with industry trends
Support the Business Manager on strategic projects as assigned

Job Requirements:

Minimum 1 years copywriting experience in writing;
Able to write excellent and stylish Cantonese;
Creative, willing to learn, self-initiative & motivated, responsible, supportive and able to work under pressure, independently and over time;
Good team player with excellent interpersonal and communication skills
Stay updated on creative trends *Immediate availability is preferred

Perfect Medical is a leading Medical Beauty group with over 50 treatment centers around the world. We strive for perfection with passion. Our team are filled with young, ambitious and driven professionals. We are now seeking for a Copywriter to join our Digital Marketing Team.

