Job duties:



As a member of Fashion Programme and work with the Fashion Team in executing various fashion promotional initiatives, including Fashion Asia Hong Kong;
Develop and implement marketing & communication, and partnership strategies of fashion related programmes;
Implement digital & social media strategy, PR & advertising for FA to maximize exposure in the regional campaigns;
Assist and support the team to organize events from start to finish according to the requirements, target audience and objectives;
Effectively handle logistics, work progresses, result and evaluation and reporting, make sure the process and documentations are in compliance with governance and administrative requirements;
Work closely with professional service providers and liaise with internal and external parties within and outside HK; and
Perform ad hoc assignments as required.



Requirements:



Bachelor degree holder who is a highly motivated and versatile individual;
2 years’ experience in event management, digital marketing and project management;
Strong verbal and written communication skills in both English and Chinese are essential (Mandarin will be an advantage);
Proactive, detailed-minded, responsible and resourceful self-starter;
Good problem solving and interpersonal skills;
Possesses good knowledge in the fashion industry;
Strictly adhere to project timeline and deadlines; and
Proficient in MS Office Application and Chinese Word Processing.

More information about Fashion Asia:
https://www.fashionasiahk.com/

Work Location: Kowloon Bay / Tsuen Wan

Interested parties are invited to apply by sending your resume with full details of education, work experience, current & expected salary, contact telephone number and earliest available date to the Human Resources Office, Hong Kong Design Centre, Unit 602, 6/F, Mill 5, The Mills, 45 Pak Tin Par Street, Tsuen Wan or by clicking “Apply Now” or email to: hr[@]hkdesigncentre.org on or before 26 January 2022. HKDC reserves the right not to make appointment for the post(s) advertised. Only short-listed candidates will be notified. All information received will be kept in strict confidence for six months and data will only be used for recruitment purpose.

Responsibilities:

Developing corporate and executive communications content, e.g. group speech, PR article in English and Chinese
Copywriting in English: producing clear, compelling copy for various mediums across all communications channels (e.g. newsletters, interview), with the aim to bring company’s overall vision, strategy and business objectives to life
Coordinate and execute the sales and marketing strategies for the Company;
Assist in writing and managing content across all social media platforms: youtube, Facebook and company website and marketing collaterals
Manage company Facebook page, Google Analytic and Adwords, Yahoo and online campaigns;
Handle and support marketing/PR activities;
Good interpersonal skills, self-motivated, hardworking & well-organized;
Good knowledge in Photoshop / Illustrator / Acrobat

Requirement:

Degree holder in Communications, Public Relations, Marketing, Business Studies or related disciplines with minimum 4 years of experience in Communications, PR or marketing.
Solid experience in Marketing Communication is essential.
Good written communication skills in English and Chinese, experience in copywriting is a plus;
Able to meet tight deadline and handle project independently
Self-motivated, well-organized and detail-minded;
Good team player with strong sense of responsibility

Responsibilities

Conceive and develop efficient and intuitive marketing strategies;
Organize and oversee advertising / communication campaigns (search engine marketing and social media etc.), exhibitions and promotional events;
Plan and manage the production of marketing materials, including leaflets, posters, newsletters, eDM and video for on-line and off-line channels;
Coordinate and liaise with internal teams, including sales teams to deliver effective marketing communications materials for different marketing programs;
Manage and liaise with agencies to produce creative and develop strategic marketing plan to support all marketing campaigns rollout;
Develop and manage the organization’s website(s) and write and optimize content for the website and social networking accounts such as Facebook;
Track and analyze website traffic flow and provide regular internal reports
Conduct market research and analysis to evaluate trends, brand awareness and competition ventures;
Undertake any other activities as assigned by supervisors

Requirements

Degree holder in Marketing, Communication or related discipline with min. 3 years of solid experience in (digital) marketing and event management;
Energetic and creative team player with excellent interpersonal and presentable skills;
Self-motivated and flexible to take new challenges in a fast-paced working environment;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, fluency in both English and Cantonese;
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Senior Marketing Executive
Immediate available is highly preferred

Interested parties please click "Apply Now" to submit your full resume stating present and expected salary.

